From c378a69a3c62ab916ad2000a40f64f54dbc96d31 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claw <claw@atlasclaw-01>
Date: Tue, 17 Feb 2026 01:23:19 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/8] fix(browser): prevent renderer process leak and session
 restore explosion

Two root causes identified for 2026-02-16 system outage (76 renderer
processes, 3.5GB memory exhaustion requiring full server restart):

## Bug 1: Chrome session restore (PRIMARY)
Chrome was restoring 1,501 URLs from accumulated session history on
every startup, creating 79+ renderer processes immediately.

Fix:
- Add --restore-last-session=false flag
- Add --disable-restore-background-contents flag
- Clear existing session data

## Bug 2: BrowserContext never closed (SECONDARY)
OpenClaw used a single shared BrowserContext that was never closed.
page.close() is called but context.close() was never called, causing
Chromium renderer processes to accumulate indefinitely.

Fix:
- closePageByTargetIdViaPlaywright(): close context when last page exits
- closePageViaPlaywright(): close context when last page exits

## New files
- browser-queue.ts: request queue for future concurrency control
- context-cleanup.ts: cleanup utilities and monitoring helpers

Tested: open + snapshot + close cycle stays at 3 renderers (vs 79).
Context cleanup confirmed: renderer freed on page close.
